20 Tips

- Avoid to use the keys on the right side of the keyboard.
- First: Learn to move.
- Begin using the visual mode to see what you are yanking.
- Use the registers, at least "0.
- Windows are easy to use with a few commands, is worth it.
- Copy your vim configuration to the remote server or mount files locally and use your local vim.
- Don't stop adding knowledge to your vim arsenal.
